{"uri":"pour-plating-of-thalassiosira-pseudonana-tp-i42cgye","version_id":"0","protocol_name":"Pour plating of Thalassiosira pseudonana (Tp)","protocol_name_html":"Pour plating of Thalassiosira pseudonana (Tp)","is_prepublished":"0","can_edit":"0","parent_id":null,"api_version":"1","is_new_mode":"0","last_modified":"1522217461","type_id":"1","link":null,"fork_id":"","public_fork_note":"","number_of_steps":"7","has_versions":"1","first_published_date":"1501016486","publish_date":"2017-07-25 21:01:26","documents":null,"have_protocol_in_step":"0","is_protocol_in_step":"0","vendor_name":"Contributed by users","vendor_link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","vendor_logo":"\/img\/vendors\/1.png","mod_mins":"-45","mod_secs":"1","description":"<p>Here we present an efficient way to grow Tp colonies inside a 0.25% superclean agar matrix. This protocol could possibly be applicable to other marine microeukaryotes that are problematic to grow on fully solid support.<\/p>","is_bookmarked":"0","can_reassign":"1","before_start":"<p><strong>1. Tp L1<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Prepare L1 medium with Aquil salts as described by Karas et al. (2015). After sterile filtration, add 5 mL 30 g\/L Na2SiO3 x 9H2O per 1L L1.\u00a0More details on exact medium preparation can be found <a href=\"http:\/\/www.openwetware.org\/images\/2\/2f\/JT_L1_Aquil_generic.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here<\/a>. This medium is referred to as 'Tp L1' in the protocol.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Reference:<\/p>\n<p>Karas, B.J. et al. (2015) Designer diatom episomes delivered by bacterial conjugation. Nature Communications. 6, 692-695.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p><strong>2. Superclean agar\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Prepare according to Waterbury &amp; Willey (1988). Excerpt:<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>'100 g of agar is washed by stirring\u00a0with 3 liters of double-distilled water in a 4-liter beaker. After 30 min of\u00a0stirring, the agar is allowed to settle, the wash water is siphoned off, and\u00a0the agar is filtered onto Whatman F4 filter paper in a Buchner funnel. This\u00a0procedure is repeated once more or until the filtrate is clear. The agar is\u00a0then washed with 3 liters of 95% ethanol followed by a final 3-liter wash\u00a0with analytical grade acetone. The agar is then dried at 50 \u00b0C in glass baking\u00a0dishes for 2-3 days and stored in a tightly covered container.'\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Use bacteriological agar from Sigma --&gt;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/catalog\/product\/sial\/a5306?lang=en&amp;region=US\" target=\"_blank\"> LINK<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Reference:<\/p>\n<p>Waterbury, J.B. &amp; Willey, J.M. 1988\u00a0Isolation and Growth of Marine\u00a0Planktonic Cyanobacteria. Methods in Enzymology, vol. 167, pp. 100-105.\u00a0<\/p>","has_guidelines":"0","materials":[],"warning":null,"version_class":"7034","public":"1","is_owner":"1","is_original_owner":"1","created_on":"1501000219","protocol_affiliation":"Harvard Medical School, Scripps Institution of Oceanography, J. Craig Venter Institute,J. Craig Venter Institute","affiliation":"Harvard Medical School, Department of Systems Biology | UC San Diego, Scripps Institution of Oceanography (SIO) | J. Craig Venter Institute (JCVI)","doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.i42cgye","doi_status":"2","changed_fork_steps":null,"profile_url":"JernejTurnsek-w2x284v2p2","protocol_img":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/mkpdtje.png","profile_image":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/tmmdtje.jpg","full_name":"Jernej Turnsek","created_by":"Jernej Turnsek","private_link":"78D78F9F6B90EDA5390E8716FE153D22","original_img":"1","username":"jernej-turnsek","is_retracted":"0","retraction_reason":null,"plos_id":null,"manuscript_citation":null,"journal_name":null,"is_donations_disabled":"0","is_donations_disabled_by_user":"9","item_record_id":225563,"fork_info":[],"compare_forks":[],"protocols":[],"groups":[{"group_id":"108","group_uri":"protg","group_name":"Protist Resea